<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br>
</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;">&quot;The IGBT Miracle: From Conception to=
 Global Impact&quot;</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;">Distinguished University Professor B. Jaya=
nt Baliga</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;">North Carolina State University</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;">Raleigh, NC 27613</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;"><em>Abstract:</em> The Insulated Gate Bip=
olar Transistor (IGBT) has had an enormous impact on creating a sustainable=
 society by enhancing the comfort and convenience of billions of people whi=
le reducing energy consumption. It
 is widely used in the consumer, industrial, transportation, lighting, medi=
cal, and renewable energy generation sectors. The greatest environmental im=
pact is due to its utilization in electronic ignition systems, adjustable s=
peed motor drives, and compact fluorescent
 lamps. During the last 25 years, this has reduced world-wide gasoline cons=
umption by 1.5 Trillion gallons and reduced electrical energy consumption b=
y more than 73,000 Terra-Watt-Hours leading to consumers saving $ 24 Trilli=
on. This talk will discuss the challenges
 that had to be overcome to commercialize the IGBT and review its wide rang=
e of applications today.</p>
